reviewText: Haunting, disturbing indie production of a repressed college professor who finds a personal and sexual outlet in doing pron.  At first it is cold research, then personal desire to feel another body, then an awakening warmth and pulse, hence her own heart beating.  A woman's exploration of self and identity, not feminist, and without complete liberation.  The female character loses as much as she's gained.  Remarkable award-winning work by director Huh Eun-hee  and late actress Yoo Donh-sook.  Not for everyone.

reviewText: The star, Yoo Dong plays a middle aged college professor who has never known love.  However, she badly wants to experience the feeling of sex and lust.  She gets into making porn and falls for her young co-star who falls for her as well- alas, they are not meant to be together.  She sacrifices too much in the end for her experience.I felt like another reviewer- it was a sad story- and I'm a guy- I felt bad for Yoo Dong.  She plays such a sad character who has naughty librarian good looks and is so innocent in the movie even after she is "with" a man.  She's the girl many good guys would love to meet.  It is a slow movie but I couldn't turn it off.  I wanted her to end up happy and fulfilled.I felt so bad at the end that I looked her up on the interweb only to find out that she died of the flu shortly after making this movie- it was released long after her death out of respect.  From reading the reviews, you'll either love it or hate it.
